{
  "info": {
    "name": "URL Shortener API",
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "description": "Advanced personal URL shortener — shorten links, manage them, and view detailed tracking analytics.\n\n**Setup:**\n1. Set the `baseUrl` collection variable to your deployment URL (default: `http://localhost:3000`).\n2. Run **Sign Up** or **Log In** — the `authToken` variable is saved automatically.\n3. *(Optional)* Run **Continue as Guest** to populate `guestId` instead.\n\n**Auth:** protected endpoints send `Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}` (logged-in users) or `X-Guest-Id: {{guestId}}` (guests). Both are pre-configured via collection variables.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:3000",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Base URL of your deployed app"
    },
    {
      "key": "authToken",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "JWT – auto-populated by Sign Up / Log In requests"
    },
    {
      "key": "guestId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "UUID for guest users – auto-populated by Continue as Guest"
    },
    {
      "key": "shortCode",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Auto-populated by the Shorten URL request"
    }
  ],
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": [""] }
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "User Auth",
      "description": "Account signup, login, and guest mode.\n\n- **Sign Up / Log In** → saves `authToken` automatically.\n- **Continue as Guest** → generates a UUID and saves it as `guestId`.\n- When you later Sign Up or Log In with a `guestId` in the body, all guest links are automatically migrated to the new account.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Sign Up",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('authToken', json.data.token);",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('guestId', '');",
                  "  console.log('authToken saved:', json.data.token);",
                  "  if (json.data.claimedUrls > 0) {",
                  "    console.log('Guest URLs migrated:', json.data.claimedUrls);",
                  "  }",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Alice Smith\",\n  \"email\": \"alice@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"secret123\",\n  \"guestId\": \"{{guestId}}\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/signup",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "signup"]
            },
            "description": "Create a new user account.\n\n**Body fields:**\n- `email` *(required)*\n- `password` *(required, min 6 chars)*\n- `name` *(optional)*\n- `guestId` *(optional)* — pass the current guest UUID to migrate all guest links to this account\n\nOn success, `authToken` is saved automatically as a collection variable."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "201 Created",
              "status": "Created",
              "code": 201,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"data\": {\n    \"token\": \"eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...\",\n    \"user\": {\n      \"_id\": \"66f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0d1\",\n      \"name\": \"Alice Smith\",\n      \"email\": \"alice@example.com\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-01T10:00:00.000Z\"\n    },\n    \"claimedUrls\": 3\n  }\n}",
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json"
            },
            {
              "name": "409 Email Already Registered",
              "status": "Conflict",
              "code": 409,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"error\": \"Email already in use.\"\n}",
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json"
            },
            {
              "name": "400 Validation Error",
              "status": "Bad Request",
              "code": 400,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"error\": \"Password must be at least 6 characters.\"\n}",
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Log In",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('authToken', json.data.token);",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('guestId', '');",
                  "  console.log('authToken saved:', json.data.token);",
                  "  if (json.data.claimedUrls > 0) {",
                  "    console.log('Guest URLs migrated:', json.data.claimedUrls);",
                  "  }",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"alice@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"secret123\",\n  \"guestId\": \"{{guestId}}\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "login"]
            },
            "description": "Authenticate with email and password.\n\nInclude `guestId` in the body to migrate any links created as a guest into this account.\n\nOn success, `authToken` is saved automatically as a collection variable."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"data\": {\n    \"token\": \"eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...\",\n    \"user\": {\n      \"_id\": \"66f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0d1\",\n      \"name\": \"Alice Smith\",\n      \"email\": \"alice@example.com\"\n    },\n    \"claimedUrls\": 0\n  }\n}",
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json"
            },
            {
              "name": "401 Invalid Credentials",
              "status": "Unauthorized",
              "code": 401,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"error\": \"Invalid email or password.\"\n}",
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Current User (me)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{authToken}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/me",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "me"]
            },
            "description": "Returns the profile of the currently authenticated user. Requires a valid JWT (`authToken`)."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"data\": {\n    \"user\": {\n      \"_id\": \"66f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0d1\",\n      \"name\": \"Alice Smith\",\n      \"email\": \"alice@example.com\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-01T10:00:00.000Z\",\n      \"updatedAt\": \"2026-03-01T10:00:00.000Z\"\n    }\n  }\n}",
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json"
            },
            {
              "name": "401 No / Invalid Token",
              "status": "Unauthorized",
              "code": 401,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"error\": \"Login required.\"\n}",
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Continue as Guest (pre-request helper)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "// Generates a UUID v4 and stores it so guest requests include X-Guest-Id.",
                  "function uuidv4() {",
                  "  return 'xxxxxxxx-xxxx-4xxx-yxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx'.replace(/[xy]/g, function(c) {",
                  "    const r = Math.random() * 16 | 0;",
                  "    return (c === 'x' ? r : (r & 0x3 | 0x8)).toString(16);",
                  "  });",
                  "}",
                  "if (!pm.collectionVariables.get('guestId')) {",
                  "  const id = uuidv4();",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('guestId', id);",
                  "  console.log('Guest ID created:', id);",
                  "} else {",
                  "  console.log('Existing guest ID:', pm.collectionVariables.get('guestId'));",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Guest ID is set', function() {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.collectionVariables.get('guestId')).to.match(",
                  "    /^[0-9a-f]{8}-[0-9a-f]{4}-4[0-9a-f]{3}-[89ab][0-9a-f]{3}-[0-9a-f]{12}$/i",
                  "  );",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/health",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "health"]
            },
            "description": "Run this request to generate a guest UUID and save it as the `guestId` collection variable. After running it, all URL Management and Analytics requests will automatically include the `X-Guest-Id` header.\n\nThe pre-request script generates the UUID; it hits `/api/health` as a simple no-op target."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Public",
      "description": "Endpoints that require no authentication.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health Check",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/health",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "health"]
            },
            "description": "Returns server status and current UTC timestamp."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"status\": \"ok\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-02-28T12:00:00.000Z\"\n}",
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Shorten URL",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('shortCode', json.data.shortCode);",
                  "  console.log('shortCode saved:', json.data.shortCode);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"url\": \"https://www.example.com/some/very/long/url/that/needs/shortening\",\n  \"customAlias\": \"\",\n  \"expiresIn\": \"30d\",\n  \"title\": \"Example Page\",\n  \"description\": \"A short description of the link\",\n  \"tags\": [\"demo\", \"example\"]\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/shorten",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "shorten"]
            },
            "description": "Creates a new short URL. On success the `shortCode` collection variable is automatically set for use in subsequent requests.\n\n**Body fields:**\n- `url` *(required)* — the original URL to shorten\n- `customAlias` *(optional)* — 3–30 char custom slug (letters, numbers, `-`, `_`)\n- `expiresIn` *(optional)* — duration string: `7d`, `24h`, `30m`, `60s`\n- `title` / `description` *(optional)* — metadata\n- `tags` *(optional)* — string array"
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "201 Created",
              "status": "Created",
              "code": 201,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"data\": {\n    \"id\": \"64f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0d1\",\n    \"shortCode\": \"aB3xY7z\",\n    \"shortUrl\": \"http://localhost:3000/aB3xY7z\",\n    \"originalUrl\": \"https://www.example.com/some/very/long/url\",\n    \"title\": \"Example Page\",\n    \"description\": \"A short description\",\n    \"tags\": [\"demo\", \"example\"],\n    \"expiresAt\": \"2026-03-29T12:00:00.000Z\",\n    \"createdAt\": \"2026-02-28T12:00:00.000Z\"\n  }\n}",
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json"
            },
            {
